</title>
<subSubSection id="6C680B027ECD1B9796C602DB866A5C79" pageId="null" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="23CDCEAE1184AFDB32A633F211AEB1B9" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">
Unterscheidet sich von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="5B26AF2BC52BB421B857B9E6F78FB00B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nymphaeaceae" genus="Nymphaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nymphaeales" pageId="null" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEB766D933AF5CC52E43271CE187A6A5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Nymphaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="46F98CE2273325859A016D6EA85EE3DE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">
<normalizedToken id="9D3A3749D96C445B1A2169A20BD2A5F6" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
aus dem Wasser ragend, rund, nicht eingeschnitten, gegen den zentralen Stiel hin meist vertieft
</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="0ED03843F54E59E4979AD2A5A4E1E397" originalValue="schalenförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">schalenfoermig</normalizedToken>
); 
<emphasis id="D4C6E7715BF465B7395DA558E944A790" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">
Fruchtknoten viele, 1 
<normalizedToken id="092119DB130DA16CCBD3BBEC900ADBBD" originalValue="blättrig" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">blaettrig</normalizedToken>
, 1 
<normalizedToken id="1E3FA5DB903EC932FD555E0B08524703" originalValue="sämig" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">saemig</normalizedToken>
, frei, bis zur Spitze in den 
<normalizedToken id="8FDD9249CA3B853CA7ED3D56FC9A32DF" originalValue="Blütenboden" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Bluetenboden</normalizedToken>
eingesenkt; 
<normalizedToken id="00C8DA9715851B645FD87FF90E22A4F4" originalValue="Früchtchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Fruechtchen</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="AB5283BCD8134CC325A9314E0D585981" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">ueber</normalizedToken>
dem Wasser reifend; 
<normalizedToken id="E5FE980C8C5C47286A08AEE5F54EB3CA" originalValue="Kronblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Kronblaetter</normalizedToken>
nach der 
<normalizedToken id="81078261617ADEA4885F6E5AD9A6A9C6" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Bluete</normalizedToken>
abfallend.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECB12B380360D7A07CF7C6D1C781489F" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="6B8A2CA7BB5DE622E2583F0A535DCFE5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="0F096C4726712B4630F03F5C2EE08972" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nelumbonaceae" genus="Nelumbo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="null" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Nelumbo</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="E0306C753414660DD34DED0BAB097461" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">umfasst</normalizedToken>
2 Arten, 
<taxonomicName id="6120B096FD8AC0F9E07762C77C4B91A4" authority="Gaertn." authorityName="Gaertn." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nelumbonaceae" genus="Nelumbo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="null" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nucifera">
N. nucifera 
<normalizedToken id="87C7A2364AE22232352770536F722103" originalValue="Gärtn" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">Gaertn</normalizedToken>
.
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
im 
<normalizedToken id="6D127F1D4829280F33FF8994FF7465AF" originalValue="südlichen" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">suedlichen</normalizedToken>
Asien und in Nordaustralien, 
<taxonomicName id="2F47FAD602888853ABEB9383E57A9996" authority="Pers. in Amerika" authorityName="Pers. in Amerika" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nymphaeaceae" genus="Nymphaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nymphaeales" pageId="null" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis id="F182682DC2475C6F4353CBD8CDC78F2D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="10">N. lutea</emphasis>
Pers. in Amerika
</taxonomicName>
zwischen 11 und 42° NB.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
